        <section>
            <title>Chapter 14</title>

            <section>
                <title>Law 1: Two Movements of the Moon</title>

                <para>The moon has two mean movements. The moon itself rotates on a small circle
                    that does not surround all of the Earth. Moon's movement on that small circle is
                    called <glossterm>mean lunar anomaly</glossterm> (אמצע המסלול). The small circle
                    (epicycle) itself rotates on a big circle (deferent) that surrounds the Earth.
                    The mean movement of the small circle on the big circle that surrounds the Earth
                    is called <glossterm>mean lunar longitude</glossterm> (אמצע הירח). </para>
            </section>

